features: ▶SVAVO Automatic Fragrance Freshener - this air freshener dispenser brings you the fragrant air automaticly by timer. You can set the spraying fragrance frequence-spray interval time from 1 to 60 minutes. Interval spray time and working mode can chosen at your preferring fragrance level; Three working modes are available among Monday to Friday, Monday to Saturday, and Monday to Sunday, working period can be set from 12:00am to 11:59pm, for example 8:00am(starting time) to 6:00pm(stop time).

▶Flexible Setting with LCD Display - Automatic aroma dispenser with LCD display operating mode provides you with convenience and enables extensive suitable usage in restaurants, hotels, public places, offices, trains, homes, airplanes and your bedroom, bathroom and living room in an effective manner.

▶Batteries Operated Aerosol Sprayer - the scent spray dispenser requires 2 pcs AA batteries (NOT INCLUDED) to operate to bring continuous and long-lasting fragrance into your bedroom, guestroom, beauty center, gym and so on. LOW BATTERY: when battery power lower than 2.3V, the perfume dispenser stops working, LCD screen only displays a battery frame icon.

▶Wall Mounted or Free Standing - The programmable air freshener can be mounted to your preferring height with screws included, 7-9 feet above the floor; or you can just put the metered fragrance dispenser standing on your bedroom desk, office table, etc.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Not that hard to program.
reviews.reviewText: I bought this air freshener because our office needed a fresh smell. The best feature is the timing program, I set it to spray before we open each day so it’s not actively spraying while we have patients there. It’s really not that hard to program, just read the manual. Works perfectly so far!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 13, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A well made product
reviews.reviewText: I just received this auto sprayer.This is the V880D programmable unit. As most that have purchased this they’re putting it on a wall or on a table I am doing something different. I live in S Fl and as most here have central AC so i thought where would be the best place to put this to cover the whole house.I installed this inside the AC return. I love that its programable as i do not have to open return to turn on or off. it fills the house with a mild not overwhelming fragrance. I did have the Glade unit but didn’t like how all you could do was set it to 9,18, 36 min sprays. So i opted to spend a-little more and I’m glad i did. This SVAVO unit is so much better in so many ways and is built to last.I had no problem programming it as i did Download the manual before receiving it but all in all very straight forward. I use the Glade cans and they fit perfectly. I can not speak for other spray cans as i only use glade but what i read Air wick will fit fine. Now for the pros/ Cons.pros;Very easy to program and it has alot of options to choose to get it tailored to your liking.Very well built look more like a commercial product then a flimsy home unit. Looks like it will accept most brands of sprays. Gives you a red/ green led warning when it’s going to spray as not to spray in you face. As this not mentioned anywhere and i think it would be good to mention that when you have to change battery’s you will NOT loose your settings. By not putting that in manual is a Con.Cons;I wish it would show the spray count on the main screen instead of having to scroll thru menu to see it.I learned this from another buyer but when programming, program the features first then the time and day. Don’t know why but it works.As i do look at reviews but not always to make my final decision to buy or not it helps. As for this product the good out way the bad by a long shot. I do feel that there are some legitimate issues with some units but I think a lot has to do with human error.I feel this is a very well made product and hope to get many year’s out of it, as long as we don’t have a shortage of air fresheners LOL 😩

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 28, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Saves Money over National brands
reviews.reviewText: I've used the National brand dispensers for years. I go thru about 3 cans of fragrance a month and I find them to be battery eaters. So with fragrance and batteries I'm spendings between $180 and $200 per year. That's $14. a month + battery cost. The dispensers micro spray about 80 times per day on the medium setting whether I'm at home or not.These although seem expensive, I have three for a cost of $84. You can program these so mine work 10 hours a day while I'm at home. 30 micro sprays a day so a can of fragrance should last almost 3 months. So first year cost with fragrance and batteries will be about $140. Up to $60 less than I spend now, and 2nd year my cost will only be about $60. for fragrance and batteries if I buy the 4 pk Airwick from Amazon for $15.30.
Por ahora todo bien espero duren mucho
